She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)
Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu Part 2

After the mysterious mana calamity, Rudeus Greyrat and his fierce student Eris Boreas Greyrat are teleported to the Demon Continent. There, they team up with their newfound companion Ruijerd Supardia—the former leader of the Superd's Warrior group—to form "Dead End," a successful adventurer party. Making a name for themselves, the trio journeys across the continent to make their way back home to Fittoa.
Following the advice he received from the faceless god Hitogami, Rudeus saves Kishirika Kishirisu, the Great Emperor of the Demon World, who rewards him by granting him a strange power. Now, as Rudeus masters the powerful ability that offers a number of new opportunities, it might prove to be more than what he bargained for when unexpected dangers threaten to hinder their travels.
(Source: MAL Rewrite)

He and she were enemies. Until he knew he had the same loneliness in a dichotomized world. They are cheap, strong, and never die. The ultimate life regeneration system "Arcadia" was born from teenage soldiers who fight by making full use of the complex regeneration <Respawn>. They were invincible boys and girls (children who transcended death) who died on the battlefield and revived. The forefront of the war in which the two great powers compete for hegemony. Akihito, a boy who leads a platoon as an ace of the United States Army, is ordered to collect confidential information that is inevitable to be wiped out because of his poor performance. However, Akihito, who has kept his companions in an unexpected battle and collapse, is isolated deep underground where complex regeneration <respawn> is impossible, along with his fateful nemesis, the elite girl Philia of the Federal Army. Two people who have opposite personalities and skills and have the worst compatibility will cooperate and aim to return to the ground. The story of the encounter and resonance between him and her who continued to die on the battlefield that never died begins!
<i>Notes: - Winner of the Gold Award in the 28th Dengeki Novel Prize.

Love is always troubling. You want to have the courage to tell someone how you feel. You want to know who he likes. You want someone to listen to your worries. You want someone to give you a push. I know how you feel, and it hurts. Because I had a past I couldn't forget. And because now I have the "power" to save them.... That's why I, Io Akashi, became an angel. "I've finally found you, the angel of Kuze High." The angel touched the girl's cheek, in order to correct Yuzuki Minato's abnormal tendency to fall in love. This is a slightly mysterious coming-of-age story where memory and love play out softly.
(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
